tip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "UDBG_Port Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 22, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Specifies the port number of the machine on which the Uniface Debugger process is listening. UDBG_Port = PortNumber For example: udbg_port=13005 Default value: First available port number, starting with 13001 File section: [install] Description The port number is automatically assigned during Uniface installation. Related Links UDBG_Machine Specifies the host identifier of the machine where the Uniface Debugger is located. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}